column1: @AOC @AyannaPressley @CoriBush you are overthinking it! When ppl used to tell me what I needed for a Congressional wardrobe. My response was “I’m a Congresswoman- if I wear it it’s Congressional” My go to is thrift shopping otherwise I feel like I’m in a uniform 💙
@christineieron @staceyabrams @AOC This just gave me chills💛

It is also important to recognize that this result leaves half the country jubilant and half frustrated and anxious. I assure my constituents that I am a representative for everyone. I hear all of your voices and will continue to fight tirelessly for all of my constituents.
I look forward to the steady leadership of President-elect Biden and VP-elect Harris to get our country out of this crisis and help our nation heal.
This has been a campaign like no other. We have been through so much as a country – an unprecedented pandemic an economic collapse and a political process that has only sharpened our divisions.
President Elect Biden has received more votes than any candidate in American history and at his side is Kamala Harris the first female Vice President of the United States.

This election has pushed participation in our most precious civic duty to new heights as we have recorded the highest voter turnout in 100 years. The security of our elections was protected and we waited anxiously as all the votes were counted.
I want to congratulate the President and Vice President-elect Joe Biden and Kamala Harris on a hard fought historic victory. https://t.co/x7ElavosxA
